{
  "id": "L9",
  "title": "Buying Clothes",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome! In this lesson, you'll learn how to buy clothes in a Dutch clothing store, or 'de kledingwinkel'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V01",
      "data": {
        "de kledingwinkel": "the clothing store"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Pardon",
        "meaning": "Excuse me"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L9_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Pardon",
        "phonetic": "[pɑrˈdɔn]",
        "tip": "The stress is on the second syllable: par-DON."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "A shop assistant will often ask 'Kan ik u helpen?'. This means 'Can I help you?'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik zoek...",
        "meaning": "I am looking for..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V02",
      "data": {
        "de trui": "the sweater"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V03",
      "data": {
        "blauw": "blue"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "When an adjective like 'blauw' comes before a noun ('de trui'), you often add an '-e'. It becomes 'de blauwe trui'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V04",
      "data": {
        "de maat": "the size"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik heb maat...",
        "meaning": "I have size..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V05",
      "data": {
        "uw": "your (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Alstublieft",
        "meaning": "Here you go / Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L9_S01",
      "title": "Asking for Assistance",
      "setting": "You are in a clothing store and need help finding an item.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Get the assistant's attention",
          "chatbot_message": null
        },
        {
          "title": "Say you are looking for a blue sweater",
          "chatbot_message": "Hallo! Kan ik u helpen?"
        },
        {
          "title": "State your size",
          "chatbot_message": "Een blauwe trui. Goede keuze. Wat is uw maat?",
          "extract_info": {
            "user_size": "Extract the user's size (e.g., S, M, L)"
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Acknowledge receiving the item",
          "chatbot_message": "Maat {user_size}. Ik heb hier een blauwe trui in uw maat. Alstublieft."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Waar zijn...?",
        "meaning": "Where are...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V06",
      "data": {
        "de paskamers": "the fitting rooms"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L9_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "paskamers",
        "phonetic": "[ˈpɑsˌkaːmərs]",
        "tip": "The stress is on the first part: PAS-ka-mers."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V07",
      "data": {
        "daar": "there"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "After trying something on, the assistant might ask: 'En, past het?'. This means 'And, does it fit?'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "De trui is...",
        "meaning": "The sweater is..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V08",
      "data": {
        "te groot": "too big"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V09",
      "data": {
        "te klein": "too small"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "The word 'te' means 'too' when used before an adjective, like 'te groot' (too big) or 'te klein' (too small)."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Geen probleem",
        "meaning": "No problem"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Heeft u...?",
        "meaning": "Do you have...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "'Heeft u' is the formal way to ask 'Do you have?'. It comes from the verb 'hebben'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V10",
      "data": {
        "een maat kleiner": "a size smaller"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V11",
      "data": {
        "een maat groter": "a size bigger"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Een moment",
        "meaning": "One moment"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L9_S02",
      "title": "Trying It On",
      "setting": "The assistant has given you a sweater. Now you need to find the fitting room and check the size.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask where the fitting rooms are",
          "chatbot_message": null
        },
        {
          "title": "Say the sweater is too big",
          "chatbot_message": "De paskamers zijn daar."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if they have a size smaller",
          "chatbot_message": "En, past het?",
          "extract_info": {}
        },
        {
          "title": "Acknowledge the new size",
          "chatbot_message": "Oh, jammer. Geen probleem. Een moment... Hier is een maat kleiner. Alstublieft."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "After trying on a new size, the assistant will likely ask 'En, past deze?', meaning 'And, does this one fit?'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Deze is perfect",
        "meaning": "This one is perfect"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik neem hem",
        "meaning": "I'll take it"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Use 'hem' to refer to 'de' words like 'de trui'. For 'het' words like 'het T-shirt', you would say 'Ik neem het'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V12",
      "data": {
        "blij": "happy / glad"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To form a simple question, you can switch the subject and the verb. For example, 'Ik kan' (I can) becomes 'Kan ik?' (Can I?)."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Waar kan ik betalen?",
        "meaning": "Where can I pay?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V13",
      "data": {
        "de kassa": "the counter / checkout"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L9_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "kassa",
        "phonetic": "[ˈkɑsaː]",
        "tip": "Stress is on the first syllable: KAS-sa."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E13",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dat is dan...",
        "meaning": "That will be..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E14",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Kan ik ... ruilen?",
        "meaning": "Can I ... return/exchange?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V14",
      "data": {
        "ruilen": "to return / to exchange"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L9_E15",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Jazeker",
        "meaning": "Yes, of course"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L9_V15",
      "data": {
        "de bon": "the receipt"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L9_S03",
      "title": "Making the Purchase",
      "setting": "You've found the right size and are now ready to pay.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Say this one is perfect and you'll take it",
          "chatbot_message": "En, past deze?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask where you can pay",
          "chatbot_message": "Heel goed! Blij dat het past."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if you can return the sweater",
          "chatbot_message": "U kunt bij de kassa daar betalen."
        },
        {
          "title": "End the conversation",
          "chatbot_message": "Dat is dan 25 euro, alstublieft. ... Jazeker. Dat kan met de bon."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}